ure on short ribs (3 tbsp) per short rib.\r\n\r\n5. Place up to 10 pieces of short ribs in tilt skillet and sear short \r\nribs for 2 minutes, or until surface caramelize. Flip and repeat on \r\nall sides.\r\n\r\n6. Remove short ribs from tilt skillet and repeat step 5 until all of \r\nthe short ribs are seared.\r\n\r\n7. Place up to 6 seared short ribs per roasting pan and reserve at \r\nroomtemperature.\r\n\r\n8. Add diced onions to the now-empty tilt kettle. Cook until aromatic, \r\nand onions are 3/4 caramelized and translucent.\r\n\r\n9. Add garlic and carrots. Cook until carrots have softened and browned.\r\n\r\n10. Add tomato paste and cook until aromatic, 2-3 minutes.\r\n\r\n11. Add celery and cook until evenly coated and soft. \r\n\r\n12. Add beef stock, thyme, and bay leaves. Bring to a quick simmer and \r\ncook for 5 minutes at a simmer.\r\n\r\n13. Pour 1 qt beef stock sauce (including vegetables) over each \r\nroasting pan of short ribs (enough to go up to half of the short rib). \r\nCover each roasting pan with foil.\r\n\r\n14. Place in preheated oven and slow roast for 2 1/2 hours or until \r\nshort ribs are fork tender.\r\n\r\n15. Take pans of short rib out of oven. Carefully remove short rib out \r\nof pans and cool down to proper handling temperature. Reserve liquid \r\nfrom roasting pans.\r\n\r\n16. Strain vegetables from cooking liquid, keeping both. Remove bay \r\nleaves from vegetables and puree remaining vegetables. Mix this puree \r\nagain with pan sauce and reserve.\r\n\r\n17. Shred short ribs and place in #200 hotel pans. Cover with cooking \r\nliquid and mix so that the beef starts to absorb the braising liquid. \r\n\r\n18. Cover each pan with plastic wrap. Be sure to punch holes in the \r\nwrap to allow steam to escape. Place in 135°F heated cabinet.","stepPictures":[]},{"step":3,"stepHeading":"Plating:","stepInstructions":"Suggested side dish: #167002 Polenta (3 oz)\r\n\r\n1. Place side dish in the center of a serving plate.\r\n\r\n2. Top with 2 oz short rib meat, about 2 grabs with serving tongs.","stepPictures":[]}],"costPerWeightExclVat":0.00,"unitId":0,"storeId":18,"status":9,"recipeAuthor":"Tim Arretche","recipeModifier":"","cookingLossPercentage":0.00,"recipeDescription":"","statusId":3}